description: Managed vm secrets on a node type on managed clusters.

commands.name: az sf managed-node-type vm-secret add
commands.summary: Add a secret to the node type.
examples: az sf managed-node-type vm-secret add -g testRG -c testCluster -n snt --source-vault-id /subscriptions/XXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX/resourceGroups/testRG/providers/Microsoft.KeyVault/vaults/testkv --certificate-url https://testskv.vault.azure.net:443/secrets/TestCert/xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx --certificate-store my
